<h1 style="font-size:clamp(24px,4vw,38px);font-weight:400;color:#fff;margin:16px 0;line-height:1.2;">Oura Ring 4: honest review after 2 months of real use — the good and the bad</h1>
<p style="font-size:17px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.55);margin-bottom:8px;">60 days wearing the Oura Ring 4 on my finger. Here's the honest review: what genuinely works, what disappoints, and whether the price is worth it.</p>
<div style="font-size:11px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.3);font-family:monospace;margin-bottom:28px;">📅 May 2026 · ⏱ 9 min read</div>
<img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1576566588028-4147f3842f27?w=800&q=80" alt="Oura Ring real analysis" style="width:100%;border-radius:12px;aspect-ratio:16/9;object-fit:cover;margin-bottom:28px;" loading="lazy"/>
<div class="verdict-box">
  <span class="verdict-box__label">⚡ VERDICT AFTER 60 DAYS</span>
  <p>The Oura Ring 4 is the best smart ring on the market. Its sleep analysis is genuinely useful and changes habits. The price plus subscription is expensive, but if you use it seriously, the value is there.</p>
</div>
<div class="article-content">
<h2>Week one: calibration and skepticism</h2>
<img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1434494878577-86c23bcb06b9?w=800&q=80" alt="First days with Oura Ring" style="width:100%;border-radius:10px;aspect-ratio:16/9;object-fit:cover;margin-bottom:20px;" loading="lazy"/>
<p>The first days are calibration. The ring learns your personal baseline of HRV, temperature and heart rate. Scores are indicative and sometimes seem random. That's normal and doesn't mean the device is malfunctioning.</p>
<p>From day 14, scores start making sense. You start seeing concrete correlations between your habits and your recovery.</p>
<h2>What actually changed after 2 months</h2>
<p>Three concrete changes the data prompted: I stopped drinking coffee after 2pm (deep sleep increased 18%), I started respecting more active rest days (readiness score stabilized above 75), and I improved my bedtime by 45 minutes (deep sleep duration increased noticeably).</p>
<p>The most valuable thing isn't the numbers themselves, but that the ring turns abstract habits into concrete, observable data.</p>
<h2>What didn't convince me</h2>
<p>The step counter is mediocre — a smartwatch does it better. The app can be overwhelming at first with so much information. And the monthly subscription remains a friction point, though the value of the insights justifies it if you use them.</p>
<div class="pros-cons">
  <div class="pros-box"><span class="pros-box__label">✓ THE GOOD</span><ul><li>Exceptionally accurate sleep analysis</li><li>HRV more reliable than any smartwatch</li><li>Comfortable to sleep in and wear daily</li><li>App with genuinely actionable insights</li></ul></div>
  <div class="cons-box"><span class="cons-box__label">✗ ROOM FOR IMPROVEMENT</span><ul><li>High price plus monthly subscription</li><li>No screen or notifications</li><li>Inaccurate step counter</li></ul></div>
</div>
<h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
<div class="faq-item"><p class="faq-item__q">Does the ring scratch with daily use?</p><p class="faq-item__a">The standard titanium model shows micro-scratches over time, especially if you work with your hands. Ceramic models are more resistant. After 2 months of intensive use, scratches are minor and don't affect functionality.</p></div>
<div class="faq-item"><p class="faq-item__q">Does the battery really last 8 days?</p><p class="faq-item__a">In normal use, yes. With continuous blood monitoring enabled it drops to about 6 days. Charging from 0% takes about 80 minutes.</p></div>
<div class="faq-item"><p class="faq-item__q">Is it worth upgrading from Oura 3 to 4?</p><p class="faq-item__a">If your Oura 3 works well, it's not urgent. Gen 4 improvements are incremental: more precise sensors, better battery and slimmer design. If starting fresh, go straight to the 4.</p></div>
<div class="faq-item"><p class="faq-item__q">What happens if I cancel the subscription?</p><p class="faq-item__a">You still see basic data: sleep, activity and readiness scores. You lose detailed insights, advanced historical trends and personalized AI recommendations.</p></div>
<div class="faq-item"><p class="faq-item__q">Is it fully waterproof?</p><p class="faq-item__a">It has IP68 protection and water resistance to 100 meters. You can swim, shower and do water sports without any problem.</p></div>
<div class="faq-item"><p class="faq-item__q">How do you choose the right size?</p><p class="faq-item__a">Oura sends a free sizing kit with plastic rings to try at home. It's essential to use it because the exact size affects measurement accuracy.</p></div>
</div>
